[agent-review] details:
Narrative:
The agent fallback feature changes parameter types from scalar to list to support multiple agent fallbacks (e.g., `--agent claude --agent codex`). The implementation is fundamentally sound: agents flow correctly through TaskDefinition → CoderConfig → runner, and fallback logic on rate limits is already implemented in runner.py. CLI parameter types changed from `Optional[str]` to `Optional[List[str]]` following existing patterns (eval_cmd uses same pattern). Three minor issues identified: (1) redundant `list()` wrapper when assigning agents—inconsistent with model/effort patterns; (2) reliance on Typer >= 0.12 multi-flag accumulation, which is satisfied by pyproject.toml but hasn't been end-to-end tested per review checklist; (3) no validation of agent names, though runner.py uses defensive .get() fallback. No security or correctness issues found; CLI overrides YAML as expected.

Findings:
- [Info] factory/cli.py:166 Remove redundant list() call: change `task.coder.agents = list(agent)` to `task.coder.agents = agent`
  description: The agent parameter is already Optional[List[str]] from Typer (line 146), so wrapping it in list() again creates an unnecessary copy. This is inconsistent with how model and effort parameters are handled—they are assigned directly without wrappers (lines 168-170).
- [Info] factory/cli.py:146 Verify Typer multi-flag accumulation works: test `factory run 'task' --agent claude --agent codex` and confirm agents list receives both values. Pattern is stable in Typer 0.12+, but runtime verification needed.
  description: The agent parameter type changed from Optional[str] to Optional[List[str]], relying on Typer >= 0.12's multi-flag accumulation feature. While pyproject.toml specifies typer[all]>=0.12 and this pattern is already used for eval_cmd (line 150), the feature has not been end-to-end tested per the review checklist ("Typer multi-value option test: run `factory run 'test' --agent a --agent b --agent c` and confirm agents list contains all three").
- [Info] factory/cli.py:146 Consider updating help text to reference workers.yaml or document valid agent names and failure behavior
  description: The help text for the agent parameter ("Agent(s) to use in order (e.g. --agent claude --agent codex for codex fallback)") does not clarify that agent names are validated against worker.agents dictionary (defined in workers.yaml). Users providing invalid agent names will only encounter errors at runtime when the runner tries to execute the command.
- [Info] factory/cli.py:956 Consider reordering poll() parameters to match run_cmd() parameter order for consistency: agent should appear earlier, closer to model/effort/crucible parameters
  description: In run_cmd() (line 146), the agent parameter appears second in the parameter list, after task_or_file. In poll() (line 956), the agent parameter appears fourth, after repo, template, workers, and max_concurrency. While not a functional issue, inconsistent ordering reduces discoverability and makes the CLI feel less polished.

